## Offboarding Flow

### Triggered By
Clicking the **Offboard Client** button.

### Confirmation Modal

```
Title:   Offboard [Client Name]?

Body:    This will lock their access to course content.
         Their Brand DNA Vault data will remain accessible.

Buttons: Cancel    |   Confirm Offboard (red)
```

### On Confirm

1. `UPDATE enrollments SET status = 'offboarded', offboarded_at = now() WHERE id = ?`
2. Show success toast: "[Name] has been offboarded"
3. Redirect to `/admin/clients`

### What Offboarding Does NOT Do
- Does **NOT** delete user account
- Does **NOT** delete Brand DNA Vault data
- Does **NOT** delete homework submissions
- Only changes enrollment `status` field

### RLS Impact After Offboarding
The RLS policy on `course_steps` checks `is_published = true` — but the **route guard** on the student-facing course page should also check enrollment status. If enrollment is offboarded, student is redirected away even if steps are published.

> Note: Add enrollment status check to the student course route guard when building the student portal (future ticket).

---

## Re-enrollment Flow

### Triggered By
Clicking the **Re-enroll Client** button (only visible when status = offboarded).

### No confirmation modal needed (less destructive action)

### On Click

1. `UPDATE enrollments SET status = 'active', offboarded_at = null WHERE id = ?`
2. Show success toast: "[Name] has been re-enrolled"
3. Page refreshes (status badge updates to Active)
4. Re-enroll button switches back to Offboard button

